René Rocher https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ren%C3%A9_Rocher 0 René Rocher, (Paris 5 August 1890 – 24 juin 1970) was a France stage actor and theater director. In 1923, René Rocher gave its name to the current Comédie-Caumartin. He was managing director of the Théâtre Antoine from 1928 to 1933, then the Théâtre du Vieux-Colombier from 1935 to 1943, and the Théâtre de l'Odéon from 1940 to 1944.
